A 20-year-old man faces charges of drug possession after he was arrested following a police search at a Westham premises, on Sunday night. Police spokesperson, Colonel Thembeka Mbele said: “On Sunday night at 9pm, detectives from Provincial Organised Crime Investigation Unit proceeded to Hexham Road, Westham in Phoenix, to execute a search warrant and a warrant of arrest. On arrival, a search was conducted at the premises and the police found 21 plastic wrappings of cocaine powder, two pieces (half-moons) of crack cocaine and a small packet containing about 3g of crack cocaine residue powder.” “A 20-year-old man was arrested and charged for possession of drugs. The street value of the recovered drugs is R12, 350,” added Col Mbele. The suspect is set to appear in the Verulam Magistrate’s Court.